<subsection xml:id="subsec-range-of-probability">
    <title>Range of Probability</title>
        <activity>
            <p>
                <m>\textbf{Work individually}</m>
            </p>
            <p>
                Draw a horizontal line labeled from 0 to 1.
            </p>
            <p>
                Place the following events on the line where you think they belong:
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            The sun will rise tomorrow
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Rolling a 3 on a fair die
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Picking a red ball from a bag with 1 red and 9 blue balls
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Getting heads on a coin
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </p>      
        </activity>
        <p>  
            <m>\textbf{key takeaway}</m>
        </p>
        <p>
             Probability is written as a number between 0 and 1
             <ul>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        <m>0</m> = Impossible event
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        <m>0.5</m> = Event is equally likely to happen or not happen
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        <m>1</m> = Certain event
                    </p>
                </li>
             </ul>   
        </p>
        <example>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    A bag contains 6 red and 2 blue marbles. What is the probability of drawing a red marble?
                </p>
            </statement>
            <solution>
                <p>
                    Total marbles <m>= 6 + 2 = 8</m>
                </p>
                <p>
                    Favorable outcomes (red) <m>= 6</m>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <md>
                        <mrow> \textbf{P(Red)} = \frac{6}{8} = 0.75</mrow>
                    </md>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <md>
                        <mrow> = 75% </mrow>
                    </md>
                </p>
                <p>
                    This is a likely event, since <m>0.75 </m> is closer to 1.
                </p>
            </solution>
        </example>
</subsection>